title.narrative: 01-01 HEALTH SYTEMS STRENGTHENING

description.narrative: 1.1. By the end of 2021 government capacity on planning, service delivery and monitoring enhanced for quality and equitable health services (HSS & PHE/HiE)., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2021, children (including newborns and adolescents) and pregnant women benefit from improved and equitable high-impact maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health interventions and behaviors.
